 could help me.</p>","post_number":13,"post_type":1,"posts_count":17,"updated_at":"2025-04-22T20:36:48.564Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":12,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":98,"readers_count":97,"score":29.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":500045,"topic_slug":"reefscape-one-button-automatic-alignment","display_username":null,"primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":33098,"username":"crh_redbird1","name":"Cole Hunt","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/crh_redbird1/{size}/237120_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":70504,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/reefscape-one-button-automatic-alignment/500045/13","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3600572,"name":"Cole Hunt","username":"crh_redbird1","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/crh_redbird1/{size}/237120_2.png","created_at":"2025-04-22T20:55:49.286Z","cooked":"<p>We use a <a href="https://github.wpilib.org/allwpilib/docs/release/java/edu/wpi/first/networktables/StructArrayPublisher.html" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">StructArrayPublisher</a>.  There is a simple example uses poses on the AdvantageScope documentation page. <a href="https://docs.advantagescope.org/tab-reference/odometry" class="inline-onebox" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">🗺 Odometry | AdvantageScope</a></p>
<p>Our implementation is just as simple. We define the region via an array of Translation2ds in the Region constructor. <a href="https://github.com/FRC-Team-4143/mainbot-2025/blob/af933ead440049fdd6b675a961c8f6d460a8c862/src/main/java/frc/mw_lib/geometry/PolygonRegion.java#L19-L34" class="inline-onebox" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">mainbot-2025/src/main/java/frc/mw_lib/geometry/PolygonRegion.java at af933ead440049fdd6b675a961c8f6d460a8c862 · FRC-Team-4143/mainbot-2025 · GitHub</a>. You can see line 30-33 are setting up the struct array publisher similar to the AdvantageScope docs example, but using the Translation2d struct instead of Pose2d.</p>
<p>Then we call <code>logPoints</code> which is a custom method that just sends a value to that previously defined publisher. That value is just the Translation2d array that was given in the class constructor. <a href="https://github.com/FRC-Team-4143/mainbot-2025/blob/af933ead440049fdd6b675a961c8f6d460a8c862/src/main/java/frc/mw_lib/geometry/PolygonRegion.java#L47-L53" class="inline-onebox" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">mainbot-2025/src/main/java/frc/mw_lib/geometry/PolygonRegion.java at af933ead440049fdd6b675a961c8f6d460a8c862 · FRC-Team-4143/mainbot-2025 · GitHub</a></p>","post_number":14,"post_type":1,"posts_count":17,"updated_at":"2025-04-22T20:55:49.286Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":13,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":91,"readers_count":90,"score":28.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":500045,"topic_slug":"reefscape-one-button-automatic-alignment","display_username":"Cole Hunt","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://docs.advantagescope.org/tab-reference/odometry","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"🗺 Odometry | AdvantageScope","clicks":5},{"url":"https://github.wpilib.org/allwpilib/docs/release/java/edu/wpi/first/networktables/StructArrayPublisher.html","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"StructArrayPublisher (WPILib API 2025.3.2)","clicks":2},{"url":"https://github.com/FRC-Team-4143/mainbot-2025/blob/af933ead440049fdd6b675a961c8f6d460a8c862/src/main/java/frc/mw_lib/geometry/PolygonRegion.java#L19-L34","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"mainbot-2025/src/main/java/frc/mw_lib/geometry/PolygonRegion.java at af933ead440049fdd6b675a961c8f6d460a8c862 · FRC-Team-4143/mainbot-2025 · GitHub","clicks":2},{"url":"https://github.com/FRC-Team-4143/mainbot-2025/blob/af933ead440049fdd6b675a961c8f6d460a8c862/src/main/java/frc/mw_lib/geometry/PolygonRegion.java#L47-L53","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"mainbot-2025/src/main/java/frc/mw_lib/geometry/PolygonRegion.java at af933ead440049fdd6b675a961c8f6d460a8c862 · FRC-Team-4143/mainbot-2025 · GitHub","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":70504,"username":"AutumnPlanet","name":null,"avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/autumnplanet/{size}/260647_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":33098,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"4143/4423 Technical Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/reefscape-one-button-automatic-alignment/500045/14","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3600582,"name":"Cole Hunt","username":"crh_redbird1","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/crh_redbird1/{size}/237120_2.png","created_at":"2025-04-22T21:05:10.594Z","cooked":"<p>It looks like your implementation is a little different than ours. You are creating a single class that just checks a preset list of points. Our implementation is meant to be universal for any size/shape of polygon. We then create multiple PolygonRegion objects to define our different field zones.</p>
<p>If you want to continue with your implementation you will need to create a Pose2d or Translation2d array for each point in your zone polygon. For example:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">Translation2d[] yellow_region = new Translation2d[]{
  new Translation2d(4.501, 6.176), 
  new Translation2d(8.768, 8.000)
};
</code></pre>
<p>I don’t fully understand your apporach, but that would be an example of a 2 point “polygon” that you could publish to NT using a StructArrayPublisher. I would expect it to just look like a line in AdvantageScope.</p>
<p>Here is an example of a Translation2d array we made for our loading station zone. It is just a Triangle in the corner of the field.</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">new Translation2d[] {
  new Translation2d(0, 0),
  new Translation2d(0, 4),
  new Translation2d(4.5, 0),
  new Translation2d(0, 0)
}
</code></pre>","post_number":15,"post_type":1,"posts_count":17,"updated_at":"2025-04-22T21:07:55.515Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":14,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":79,"readers_count":78,"score":30.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":500045,"topic_slug":"reefscape-one-button-automatic-alignment","display_username":"Cole Hunt","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":33098,"username":"crh_redbird1","name":"Cole Hunt","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/crh_redbird1/{size}/237120_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":33098,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"4143/4423 Technical Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/reefscape-one-button-automatic-alignment/500045/15","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3600651,"name":"Dan","username":"tekdemo","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/tekdemo/{size}/138330_2.png","created_at":"2025-04-22T22:06:05.984Z","cooked":"<p>You can! The Field2D object supports arbitrary objects via field.getObject(“name”). Our testing consisted of</p>
<ul>
<li>Simulating the chassis</li>
<li>Grabbing the nearest tag, and then setting a pose for it on a field</li>
<li>Generating appropriate transforms, adding those to the field</li>
<li>Repeating for any other items of interest</li>
</ul>
<p>If you want to actually make lines, you can use the <code>.setPoses(....)</code>  method , and then change the display style on the dashboard. At least on Glass, there’s a number of display options to get really useful visualizations. Not sure about Advantagescope specifically. You can also setPoses using field trajectories, and do other interesting things on it, such as setting a specific object name to an image.</p>","post_number":16,"post_type":1,"posts_count":17,"updated_at":"2025-04-22T22:06:05.984Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":9,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":59,"readers_count":58,"score":36.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":500045,"topic_slug":"reefscape-one-button-automatic-alignment","display_username":"Dan","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":70504,"username":"AutumnPlanet","name":null,"avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/autumnplanet/{size}/260647_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":44763,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"2811 Programming Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/reefscape-one-button-automatic-alignment/500045/16","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3600661,"name":null,"username":"AutumnPlanet","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/autumnplanet/{size}/260647_2.png","created_at":"2025-04-22T22:10:49.